<subSubSection id="9787FDAC441C6F27FF120B7EFD927648" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DF22AE27441C6F24FF120B7EFA407558" blockId="29.[192,1441,1282,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FF120B7EFEE77578" bold="true" box="[192,316,1282,1306]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. Based on a series of 
<specimenCount id="C99B65AE441C6F24FD910B7EFD687578" box="[579,691,1282,1306]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="male">19 males</specimenCount>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB0CD3D6441C6F24FD6D0B7EFCB97578" author="Young, R. M." box="[703,866,1282,1306]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" refId="ref26743" refString="Young, R. M. 1988. A monograph of the genus Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum 11: vi + 115 p." type="book" year="1988">Young (1988)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="189DD5A4441C6F24FC370B7EFB767578" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1988" box="[997,1197,1282,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mescalerensis">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FC370B7EFB767578" box="[997,1197,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. mescalerensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Mescalero Sand Dunes, Chaves County, 
<collectingRegion id="1D5960C5441C6F24FDFD0B5EFD137558" box="[559,712,1314,1338]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
. The female was subsequently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="BB0CD3D6441C6F24FB340B5EFA4C7558" author="La Rue, D. A." box="[1254,1431,1314,1338]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="23 - 37" refId="ref24046" refString="La Rue, D. A. 1998. Notes on Polyphylla Harris with a description of a new species (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Insecta Mundi 1 / 2: 23 - 37." type="journal article" year="1998">La Rue (1998)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF22AE27441C6F24FF220B3EFD1F75B8" blockId="29.[192,1441,1282,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
In Young’s key to the North American species of 
<taxonomicName id="189DD5A4441C6F24FC860B3EFC0C7538" baseAuthorityName="Russell" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[852,983,1346,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FC860B3EFC0C7538" box="[852,983,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Polyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(1988), the concluding couplet for 
<taxonomicName id="189DD5A4441C6F24FA550B3EFEB37518" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mescalerensis">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FA550B3EFEB37518" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. mescalerensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(#18, p.24) includes the distributional note, “ 
<collectingRegion id="1D5960C5441C6F24FC490B1EFBF37518" box="[923,1064,1378,1402]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A78AEEB7441C6F24FBE70B1EFB4B7518" box="[1077,1168,1378,1402]" name="Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.” Inexplicably, no further reference to the Chihuahuan record appears anywhere in the publication nor, in the intervening years since Young’s publication, have any supporting references documenting its occurrence there been reported (
<bibRefCitation id="BB0CD3D6441C6F24FEEA0BBEFE1575B8" author="Moron, M. A." box="[312,462,1474,1498]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="205 - 264" refId="ref24575" refString="Moron, M. A. 1997. Melolonthinae. p. 205 - 264. In: M. A. Moron, B. C. Ratcliffe, and C. Deloya (eds.). Atlas de los Escarabajos de Mexico. Coleoptera: Lamellicornia Vol. I. Familia Melolonthidae. Comision Nacional para el Conocimiento y Uso de la Biodiversidad (CONABIO) y Sociedad Mexicana de Entomologia; A. C., Mexico. 280 p." type="book chapter" year="1997">Morón 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB0CD3D6441C6F24FE080BBEFDC375B8" author="Moron, M. A." box="[474,536,1474,1498]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref24660" refString="Moron, M. A. 2010. Las especies Americanas de Polyphylla Harris (Coleoptera: Melolonthidae: Melolonthinae): biologia e importancia agricola. p. 1 - 17. In: L. A. Rodriguez-del-Bosque, and M. A. Moron (eds.). Ecologia y control de plagas edaficolas. Publicacion especial del Instituto de Ecologia; A. C., Mexico 329 p." type="book chapter" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<quantity id="186503C2441C6F24FDF70BBDFD5B75BB" box="[549,640,1473,1497]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1181" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="2015.0">
2015 
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FDB50BBEFD5B75BB" box="[615,640,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">in</emphasis>
</quantity>
litt.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF22AE27441C6F24FF220B9EFC527638" blockId="29.[192,1441,1282,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
A purported male specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="189DD5A4441C6F24FDBA0B9EFCEB7598" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1988" box="[616,816,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mescalerensis">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FDBA0B9EFCEB7598" box="[616,816,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. mescalerensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
examined is labeled “ 
<collectingCountry id="A78AEEB7441C6F24FBEE0B9EFBA47598" box="[1084,1151,1506,1530]" name="Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">MEX</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="1D5960C5441C6F24FB580B9EFAC37598" box="[1162,1304,1506,1530]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
, Cerro San Luis, 
<date id="AB2388E7441C6F24FED0087EFE7A7678" box="[258,417,1538,1562]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" value="1981-08-13">VIII-13-1981</date>
, 1767m at light, S. McCleve // 
<taxonomicName id="189DD5A4441C6F24FCD6087EFBC67678" authority="Young" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1988" box="[772,1053,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mescalerensis">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FCD6087EFC1C7678" box="[772,967,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. mescalerensis</emphasis>
Young
</taxonomicName>
, det. R. M. 
<bibRefCitation id="BB0CD3D6441C6F24FB4C087EFAF07678" author="Young, R. M." box="[1182,1323,1538,1562]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" refId="ref26743" refString="Young, R. M. 1988. A monograph of the genus Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum 11: vi + 115 p." type="book" year="1988">Young 1988</bibRefCitation>
” (DALC). The coincidental year of Young’s determination suggests the possibility that this was a specimen on which he validated the Chihuahuan distributional record.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF22AE27441C6F24FF22081EFC0676F8" blockId="29.[192,1441,1282,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Upon closer scrutiny, however, the Cerro San Luis specimen and samples from the Mescalero Sand Dunes differ in several salient morphological respects as follows:</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF22AE27441C6F27FF1208BEFB9D74E8" blockId="29.[192,1440,1729,1914]" lastBlockId="30.[192,1441,1106,1418]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FF1208BEFE2D76B8" bold="true" box="[192,502,1729,1754]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Mescalero Sand Dunes,</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="6FF5A47A441C6F24FE2908BEFD667698" collectorName="Dorsal" location="New Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" specimenCount="15" specimenCount-male="15" stateProvince="New Mexico">
<emphasis id="EDE97235441C6F24FE2908BEFD7E76BB" bold="true" box="[507,677,1729,1754]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<collectingRegion id="1D5960C5441C6F24FE2908BEFD7B76BB" box="[507,672,1729,1754]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
.
</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount id="C99B65AE441C6F24FD6108BDFCCB76B8" box="[691,784,1729,1754]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="male">15 male</specimenCount>
topotypes) (
<figureCitation id="47A6B2A2441C6F24FC4C08BEFC2976B8" box="[926,1010,1730,1754]" captionStart="Figures 48–49" captionStartId="30.[192,298,996,1020]" captionTargetBox="[402,1147,200,956]" captionTargetId="figure-280@30.[402,1158,200,956]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figures 48–49. Polyphylla. Males. 48) Polyphylla mescalerensis Young [topotype]. Mescalero Sand Dunes, Chaves County, New Mexico. 49) Polyphylla sp. incertae. Cerro San Luis, Chihuahua, Mexico." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353402/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). 
<collectorName id="7268CBF1441C6F24FBD608BEFB8F76B8" box="[1028,1108,1730,1754]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Dorsal</collectorName>
integument light yellowishbrown to reddish-brown except head black
</materialsCitation>
; anterior clypeal margin moderately reflexed, lateral margins basally convergent; distal maxillary palpomere-4 conical, obtusely tapered at apex, surface coarsely punctate, with only a few randomly scattered golden setae; scutellum narrow, triangular; pronotum widest at basal 1/2, margins strongly explanate, discal setae sparsely to moderately distributed; elytral disc setose or glabrous (abrasion), posterior margins obtusely rounded; protibia bidentate to tridentate; meta-, mesotibia with two or three acuminate projections; antennae small, slightly to deeply recurved distally; ventral surface of protarsomere-5 smooth, lacking any serration.
</paragraph>
